The paper deals with the problem of visually-guided audio source separation, which involves processing both visual and audio information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SD (Sound), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.SI (Sound and Music Computing), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.SD and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of separating sounds from visual objects. cs.SI and cs.MM are also relevant, as they deal with sound and multimedia processing, respectively. Finally, cs.LG is a possible category, as the paper uses deep neural networks for training and inference.
